cs.SE, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.HC. 

This paper focuses on sentiment analysis of developers' communication traces in software development, specifically in the context of Stack Overflow. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). However, since the paper also involves natural language processing techniques for emotion analysis, it could also fit into cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential impact of emotion awareness on software development, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
